ODE X

TO MERCURY

RANDSON of Atlas, Mercury, ’twas thine, The new-born man’s rude manners to refine, By speech to school the mind, by gracious game To shape the [rame.

Envoy of gods and mighty Jove their sire,

Ι sing thy praise, thou parent of the lyre ς
